(45, 1, '2021-04-10 09:09:34', '2021-04-10 09:09:34', '<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"alignfull\" style=\"background-image:url(\'http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/skyline-cropped-scaled-1.jpg\');\n  height: 100vh;\n  background-position: center;\n  background-repeat: no-repeat;\n  background-size: cover;\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"alignwide\"} -->\n<p class=\"alignwide\"><em><strong>TL;DR: </strong>Particulate matter level in Abu Dhabi has been decreasing over the past few years; however, it still remains higher than the WHO\'s annual limit. Thus, monitoring air quality and taking actions to protect our respiratory well-beings is of significant importance.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\">1. The Good</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are currently over 20 air quality monitoring stations across the Emirate of Abu Dhabi, reporting data on:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Particulate matter (PM)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ozone (O<sub>3</sub>)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nitrogen dioxide (NO<sub>2</sub>)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Sulfur dioxide (SO<sub>2</sub>)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This network of monitoring stations (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://adairquality.ae/\" target=\"_blank\">adairquality.ae</a>) is a great initiative to keep track of air quality as a part of the regulatory process towards a more sustainable-living future in the UAE.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Annually, the Environment Agency – Abu Dhabi (EAD) publish a summary report from this network of monitoring stations. It is evident that there is a downward trend since 2012 for PM10 (coarse particulate matter). On the other hand, PM2.5 (fine particulate matter) witnessed a slight upward trend, albeit with a recent sharp drop from 2018 to 2019.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\",\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery alignwide has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":55,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-55\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":53,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-53\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-caption wp-element-caption\">Source: <a href=\"https://www.ead.gov.ae/-/media/Project/EAD/EAD/Documents/Resources/Air-Quality-Annual-Report-2019.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Air Quality Annual Summary Report Abu Dhabi 2019 Environment Agency Abu Dhabi, 2019</a>.<br></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Independently, the US Embassy at Abu Dhabi and US Consulate at Dubai also measures PM2.5 level and provides public access to the data via <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.airnow.gov/international/us-embassies-and-consulates/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.airnow.gov/international/us-embassies-and-consulates/\" target=\"_blank\">AirNow</a> program. It is evident that there has been a recent downward trend in PM2.5 level between 2019 and 2020 from this data source:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":49,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image-1024x191.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-49\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">PM2.5 raw concentration in Abu Dhabi and Dubai <br>Source: IQ Air <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.iqair.com/us/world-most-polluted-cities?continent=&amp;country=&amp;state=&amp;page=1&amp;perPage=50&amp;cities=cxZKhW7CswiwJtEb5,ddb9n6wJjtYneTR4n,\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.iqair.com/us/world-most-polluted-cities?continent=&amp;country=&amp;state=&amp;page=1&amp;perPage=50&amp;cities=cxZKhW7CswiwJtEb5,ddb9n6wJjtYneTR4n,\" target=\"_blank\">World\'s most polluted cities 2020 (PM2.5)</a></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This comes at no surprise considering the COVID-19 pandemic has led to a significant reduction in emission activities. Whether this downward trend in emission across the world continues or not is up for debate<sup>[1]</sup>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On top of that, particulate matter concentration in the UAE exhibits a strong seasonal fluctuation, with highest peaks in the summer and lower levels in winter months. This phenomenon likely linked to  frequent dust storm in the summer coupled with increased energy demand<sup>[2]</sup>. As most people stay indoors during the summer, they inadvertently lower their exposure to the highest PM concentrations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":244,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image-7-1024x531.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-244\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Al-Taani et. al. \"Fig. 4 Monthly average of ambient PM2.5 in UAE from 1980 to 2016\"<sup>[2]</sup><br>[Y-axis: Raw concentration of PM2.5 (μg/m<sup>3</sup>)</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\"><br>2. The Bad</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That said, annual PM2.5 concentration is still 2 to 4 times higher than the limit set by WHO <strong>(10μg/m<sup>3</sup>)</strong> over the past 3 years. In fact, all the UAE population are subjected to annual average PM2.5 levels higher than the guidelines of WHO<sup>[2]</sup>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Research has shown that while environmental disease burden in the UAE is lower than global average, outdoor air quality remains the number one leading factor for premature death<sup>[3]</sup>. In fact, a 2013 study found that 7.3% of all deaths in the UAE could be attributed to outdoor air pollution.<sup>[4]</sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Air quality in Abu Dhabi and the region as a whole is a complex and dynamic issue due to its unique geographic and socioeconomic characteristics. Located in an arid region with little vegetation, Abu Dhabi is often prone to natural dust storms and dust events that result in high concentration of particulate matter, during which people, especially those with pre-existing respiratory conditions, are strongly advised to stay indoors<sup>[5][6]</sup>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":232,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/20180513-mideastsand.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-232\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Dust storm in the Middle East as seen from space<br>Credit: <a href=\"https://www.nesdis.noaa.gov/content/dust-storm-persian-gulf\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.nesdis.noaa.gov/content/dust-storm-persian-gulf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">NOAA National Environmental Satellite, Data, and Information Service (NESDIS)</a></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While natural pollutants such as dust storms make up most of the coarser particulate matter (PM10), anthropogenic emissions (traffic, refineries, water desalination plants, construction activities...) contribute to fine and ultrafine particulate matter (PM2.5)<sup>[7]</sup>. Remember: the smaller the particulate matter, the more dangerous it it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The photo below shows particulate matter collected on Teflon filters during different occasions in the UAE. On days with dust storms, the color is noticeably yellow. However, on \"clearer\" days whiteout dust stroms, the color is much darker, which can be attributed to black (elemental) carbon and anthropogenic emissions:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":186,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-186\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Hamdan et. al. \"Fig 1. Images for three samples showing the variation of color due to different sources of pollutants\", 2016<sup>[4]</sup></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Without getting into the scientific details of air pollution, it is worth noting that anthropogenic air pollutants such as SO<sub>2</sub> and NO<sub>2</sub> can also interact with natural pollutants to create secondary pollutants, exacerbating air quality<sup>[5]</sup>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\">3. The Future</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The UAE is supporting ongoing efforts to curb emission and adapt sustainable-living strategies to reduce the mortality rate from household and ambient air pollution from 64.8 (2017) to 60.2 per 100,000 by 2030<sup>[8]</sup>. One thing we can all hope for is that the decreasing trend in air pollution in the UAE continues well into the near future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the same time, it will take years for the top-down approach to systematically reduce pollutant levels below the recommended guideline by the WHO. In the immediate future, we can all do our parts by adopting a more conscious approach to quantifying air quality and reduce our personal exposure to air pollution, which will be explored in the final article of this series: <a href=\"/ways-to-protect-yourself/\">3. Ways to protect yourself</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"opacity\":\"css\",\"className\":\"is-style-dots\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity is-style-dots\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\">Citation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Gardiner, Beth. \"Why COVID-19 Will End Up Harming The Environment\".&nbsp;<em>Science</em>, 2021, <a href=\"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/article/why-covid-19-will-end-up-harming-the-environment\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/article/why-covid-19-will-end-up-harming-the-environment</a>. Accessed 11 Apr 2021.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Al-Taani, A.A., Nazzal, Y., Howari, F.M.&nbsp;<em>et al.</em>&nbsp;Long-term trends in ambient fine particulate matter from 1980 to 2016 in United Arab Emirates.&nbsp;<em>Environ Monit Assess</em>&nbsp;<strong>191,&nbsp;</strong>143 (2019). <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/s10661-019-7259-9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://doi.org/10.1007/s10661-019-7259-9</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Gibson, Jacqueline MacDonald, and Zeinab S. Farah. \"Environmental risks to public health in the United Arab Emirates: a quantitative assessment and strategic plan.\"&nbsp;<em>Environmental health perspectives</em>&nbsp;120.5 (2012): 681-686.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Gibson, Jacqueline MacDonald, et al. \"Deaths and medical visits attributable to environmental pollution in the United Arab Emirates.\"&nbsp;<em>PloS one</em>&nbsp;8.3 (2013): e57536.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hamdan, Nasser M., Hussain Alawadhi, and Najeh Jisrawi. \"Particulate matter pollution in the United Arab Emirates: elemental analysis and phase identification of fine particulate pollutants.\"&nbsp;<em>Proceedings of the 2nd world congress on new technologies</em>. 2016.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bardsley, Daniel. Dust storms prompt concerns over UAE\'s air quality. The National, 2018. Accessed April 7, 2021. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/environment/dust-storms-prompt-concerns-over-uae-s-air-quality-1.755594\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/environment/dust-storms-prompt-concerns-over-uae-s-air-quality-1.755594</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hamdan, Nasser M., Hussain Alawadhi, and Najeh Jisrawi. \"Elemental and Chemical Analysis of PM10 and PM2. 5 Indoor and Outdoor Pollutants in the UAE.\"&nbsp;<em>International Journal of Environmental Science and Development</em>&nbsp;6.8 (2015): 566.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>UAE National Air Quality Strategy (2021-2031), Stakeholders Workshop: Global Green Growth Institute (GGGI); 2020. Accessed April 7, 2021. <a href=\"https://gggi.org/uae-national-air-quality-strategy-2021-2031-stakeholders-workshop/\">https://gggi.org/uae-national-air-quality-strategy-2021-2031-stakeholders-workshop/</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"right\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-right\">Next Articles</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"right\",\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"has-text-align-right\"><a href=\"/ways-to-protect-yourself/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"../ways-to-protect-yourself/\">3. Ways to protect yourself</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Previous Articles</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"/what-is-particulate-matter/\">1. What is particulate matter air pollution?</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Particulate Matter in Abu Dhabi', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'particulate-matter-in-abu-dhabi', '', '', '2021-04-10 09:09:34', '2021-04-10 09:09:34', '', 0, 'https://nyuadair.com/?page_id=45', 0, 'page', '', 0),
