(110, 1, '2021-04-05 11:00:46', '2021-04-05 11:00:46', '<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"alignwide\"} -->\n<p class=\"alignwide\"><em><strong>TL;DR:</strong> Particulate matter is microscopic, thus capable of penetrating deep into our lungs and bloodstream, causing damage to our bodies. While there are other kinds of air pollution, such as ground-level ozone, nitrogen dioxide... this article focuses on particulate matter as it poses the most significant threat to our health.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<section class=\"alignfull\" id=\"explanation\" style=\"margin:0;padding:0; color:white\">\n            <div class=\"container\">\n                \n                <div class=\"row\">\n                    <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\n<h2>1. Microscopic Size\n</h2>\n                        <p>\n                            Particulate matter (PM) consists of microscopic particles small enough to be suspended in the air for a long period of time. Depends on the size of the particles, particulate matter can be further broken down to: PM10 (coarse particles less than 10 micrometers across) and PM2.5 (very fine particles less than 2.5 micrometers across). PM2.5 particles are often the direct result of human-made activities, such as coal and diesel burning, vehicle emission, construction site, and agriculture waste combustion.\n                        </p>\n<h2>2. Microscopic Comparison\n</h2>\n                        <p>\n                            Tiny as they are, PM2.5 particles are invisible to our naked eyes. The background of this page is an image of a single human hair magnified 1,000 - 10,000 times depending on your screen size. Scroll down to see how particulate matter compares.\n                        </p>\n\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"items\">\n                    <div class=\"item-wrapper aligncenter\">\n                        <h4>\n                            Human hair<br>50 µm (0.05 mm)\n                        </h4>\n\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-wrapper aligncenter\">\n                        <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nguyenvince/visualizing-pm2.5-pollution/main/assets/coarse-particle.png\" class=\"img-fluid\">\n                        <h4>\n                            Coarse particle PM10<br>10 µm\n                        </h4>\n\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-wrapper aligncenter\">\n                        <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nguyenvince/visualizing-pm2.5-pollution/main/assets/red-blood-cell.png\" class=\"img-fluid\">\n                        <h4>\n                            Red blood cell<br>7 µm\n                        </h4>\n\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-wrapper aligncenter\">\n                        <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nguyenvince/visualizing-pm2.5-pollution/main/assets/fine-particle.png\" class=\"img-fluid\">\n                        <h4>\n                            Fine particle PM2.5<br>&lt;2.5 µm\n                        </h4>\n\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-wrapper aligncenter\">\n                        <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nguyenvince/visualizing-pm2.5-pollution/main/assets/coronavirus.png\" class=\"img-fluid\">\n                        <h4>\n                            Coronavirus<br>0.1 µm\n                        </h4>\n\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"row\">\n                    <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\n<h2>3. Microscopic Killer\n</h2>\n                        <p style=\"padding-bottom: 0;\">\n                            As we can see, particulate matter, especially PM2.5 particles, is on the same size magnitude of our cells. Because of this, they can bypass our first line of defense mechanism, such as nasal hairs and mucus. PM2.5 are capable of penetrating deep into our alveoli (tiny air sacks that line the lungs), from which they find their ways into our bloodstream and into other organs, such as the brain, liver, and kidney. As some of their chemical compositions include heavy metals and toxins from anthropogenic activities, they are capable of causing inflammation, oxidative stress, blockage, and ultimately cancer. Acute symptoms such as coughing, sore throat, and breathing difficulty can also occur when exposed to high levels of particulate matter.\n                        </p>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n            </div>\n\n        </section>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"opacity\":\"css\",\"className\":\"is-style-dots\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity is-style-dots\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"right\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-right\">Next Articles</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"right\",\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-right\"><a href=\"/particulate-matter-in-abu-dhabi\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"../particulate-matter-in-abu-dhabi\">2. Particulate matter in Abu Dhabi</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"right\",\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-right\"><a href=\"/ways-to-protect-yourself\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"../ways-to-protect-yourself\">3. Ways to protect yourself</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'What is Particulate Matter', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-is-particulate-matter', '', '', '2023-09-26 17:16:12', '2023-09-26 13:16:12', '', 0, 'https://nyuadair.com/?page_id=110', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(172, 1, '2021-04-13 07:53:07', '2021-04-13 07:53:07', '<!-- wp:html -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote alignwide\"><h4 style=\"margin:1rem auto\"><i>Any level of air pollution, no matter how low, is harmful to human health</i></h4><cite>Piazza, Geri. \"Air pollution linked to risk of premature death\", National Institute of Health, 2018. https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/air-pollution-linked-risk-premature-death</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\">1. Tracking Air Quality</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As discussed in the previous article, it is in our best interest to explore different ways we can protect yourself against air pollution. Tracking air quality is one of them: knowing is knowledge. Often time, air pollution is an invisible problem (except for dust storm events). Fortunately, there is a plethora of websites that provide real-time air quality data. Most of them use a combination of data from official monitoring stations (which can be few and far between) and satellite imagery with sophisticated algorithms to estimate air pollution levels:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://aqicn.org/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://aqicn.org/\" target=\"_blank\">AQICN</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.iqair.com/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.iqair.com/\" target=\"_blank\">IQAir</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://plumelabs.com/en/air/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://plumelabs.com/en/air/\" target=\"_blank\">Plumelab</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image-5-1024x467.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-198\"><figcaption><em>A quick Google search for Abu Dhabi AQI (Air quality index) returns hundreds of thousands of results</em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, due to data-aggregating nature of these websites, real-time data and the way these data is visualized varies quite a lot. A value of 100 might mean Moderate for one site or Unhealthy for others.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That is precisely the reason why this project is born: to provide our NYUAD community a <strong>localized and granular </strong>network of air quality monitors across campus. It implements the US Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.airnow.gov/aqi/aqi-basics/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.airnow.gov/aqi/aqi-basics/\" target=\"_blank\">air quality index</a> standard, which is the most widely-used system in the world. With its real-time and localized data, it can aid in understanding air pollution and making conscious health decisions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\">2. Comparing Different Protective Measures</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many easy ways we can take to reduce our exposure to harmful levels of particulate air pollution:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Being indoor</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In general, indoor air quality can be good if the building comes with a modern integrated HVAC system equipped with air filters. However, indoor microscopic dust concentration can vary considerably from household to household. Air quality can become worse if windows are not appropriately closed when the air is dirty outside. At the same time, emission activities without proper ventilation, such as smoking, cooking, and dusting... can significantly degrade indoor air quality.<sup>[3]</sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":237,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/window-opened-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-237\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Close your window when the outdoor air is unsatisfactory.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cooking is often a source of emission that we don\'t pay attention to but can have a negative impact on the air quality, especially grilled and fried food that emits <strong>carcinogenic </strong>volatile compounds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>HEPA filter</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>HEPA filter, which stands for <strong>high-efficiency particulate air filter</strong>, can successfully filter out 99.95% of airborne particles smaller than 2.5μm. Made from tightly-packed non-woven fibers, HEPA filters are used in air purifiers and modern HVAC system. It has been estimated that such systems can reduce premature mortality caused by air pollution by up to 2.5%<sup>[7]</sup>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":218,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/hepa-filter-comparison-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-218\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A <strong>HEPA filter used for 2 months (~8 hours a day) versus a new filter. Even though the  building already comes with its own HVAC filtering system, the amount of pollutants caught by the filter is staggering.</strong></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":219,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/DIY-filter-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-219\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A DIY HEPA filtering system can be an inexpensive and easy way to curb exposure to indoor air pollution, especially for those who suffer respiratory illnesses or allergies.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Cloth mask and surgical mask</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":213,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cloth-mask-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-213\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cloth masks, bandanas, and cloth handkerchiefs are often used thanks to their inexpensive price and reusability. They provide a certain degree of protection especially against larger particles; however, they only offer marginal shield against PM2.5 particles. The tighter the fabric is, the better the protection.<sup>[4][5][6]</sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.universityofcalifornia.edu/sites/default/files/surgical-mask-photo.jpg\" alt=\"Which type of face covering works best? | University of California\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Disposable surgical masks are affordable, convenient, and moderately effective against fine dust particles. If <strong>tightly worn</strong>, surgical masks can filter between 30%-80% particles while also protecting against water droplets that can carry bacteria and viruses<sup>[4][5][6]</sup>. However, due to its being mass-produced, tight fit is difficult to achieve for everyone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>N95 mask</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":217,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://bqf.lmn.temporary.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/N95-masks.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-217\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>N95 masks, if worn properly, can filter at least 95% particulate&nbsp;matter. They are commonly utilized by construction workers and healthcare workers for their great efficiency. During the past few years, N95 masks have gained considerable popularity among people in China and India as they face some of the worst air pollution episodes.<sup>[4][5][6]</sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide\">Citation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<ol>\n<li>Wei Y, Wang Y, Di Q, Choirat C, Wang Y, Koutrakis P, Zanobetti A, Dominici F, Schwartz JD. Short term exposure to fine particulate matter and hospital admission risks and costs in the Medicare population: time stratified, case crossover study. BMJ. 2019 Nov 27;367:l6258. PMID: 31776122; PMCID: PMC6880251.<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.l6258\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.l6258</a></li>\n                            <li>Schlanger, Zoë “Legal Levels of Air Pollution Are Killing the Elderly.” Quartz, Quartz, 27 Dec. 2017. <a href=\"https://qz.com/1166010/air-pollution-even-at-levels-that-meet-national-standards-causes-premature-death/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://qz.com/1166010/air-pollution-even-at-levels-that-meet-national-standards-causes-premature-death/</a></li>\n<li>Chun Chen, Bin Zhao, Review of relationship between indoor and outdoor particles: I/O ratio, infiltration factor and penetration factor,\n                                Atmospheric Environment,\n                                Volume 45, Issue 2,\n                                2011,\n                                Pages 275-288,\n                                ISSN 1352-2310. <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.atmosenv.2010.09.048\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://doi.org/10.1016/j.atmosenv.2010.09.048</a></li>\n                            <li>Shakya, K., Noyes, A., Kallin, R. et al. Evaluating the efficacy of cloth facemasks in reducing particulate matter exposure. J Expo Sci Environ Epidemiol 27, 352–357 (2017). <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/jes.2016.42\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://doi.org/10.1038/jes.2016.42</a></li>\n                            <li>Bowen, Larry E. “Does That Face Mask Really Protect You?” Applied Biosafety, vol. 15, no. 2, June 2010, pp. 67–71. <a href=\"10.1177/153567601001500204\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">doi:10.1177/153567601001500204</a></li>\n                            <li>Langrish, Jeremy P et al. “Beneficial cardiovascular effects of reducing exposure to particulate air pollution with a simple facemask.” Particle and fibre toxicology vol. 6 8. 13 Mar. 2009. <a href=\"https://dx.doi.org/10.1186%2F1743-8977-6-8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://dx.doi.org/10.1186%2F1743-8977-6-8</a></li>\n                            <li>Zhao, D.; Azimi, P.; Stephens, B. Evaluating the Long-Term Health and Economic Impacts of Central Residential Air Filtration for Reducing Premature Mortality Associated with Indoor Fine Particulate Matter (PM2.5) of Outdoor Origin. Int. J. Environ. Res. Public Health 2015, 12, 8448-8479.<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.3390/ijerph120708448\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://doi.org/10.3390/ijerph120708448</a></li>\n</ol>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Previous Articles</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"/what-is-particulate-matter/\">1. What is particulate matter air pollution?</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"left\",\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"has-text-align-left\"><a href=\"/particulate-matter-in-abu-dhabi/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"../particulate-matter-in-abu-dhabi/\">2. Particulate matter in Abu Dhabi</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->', 'Ways to Protect Yourself', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ways-to-protect-yourself', '', '', '2021-04-13 07:53:07', '2021-04-13 07:53:07', '', 0, 'https://nyuadair.com/?page_id=172', 0, 'page', '', 0),
